description:
This is a 6 minute workout called 'Glacier View Cool-Down' from the channel Laine Karwoski.
The workout falls under Cool-down/Cool-down.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Reboot Workout and The Nature Flow vibe.
The The Reboot Workout vibe means Deep stretch, low stress, total-body refresh. This is especially good for Recovery days, stress relief, post-travel stiffness. The The Nature Flow vibe means Breath-centered, full-body, outdoor rhythm. This is especially good for When you want fresh air, nature, and full-body movement..
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Glide towards the Fox Glacier with Laine and Mike in this steady cool-down.

Max rhythm: 20, Format: Steady...
